1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:37,495
<i>Don't worry, dear. Okay?</i>

2
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:39,873
<i>No one will bother Mikoy anymore.</i>

3
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:43,835
- Are you sure you're not hurt?
- Nothing.

4
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:45,837
<i>The one who attacked you</i>
<i>was Jepoy's brother.</i>

5
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:49,048
And according to him,
he was only avenging his brother.

6
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:54,345
there's only one thing we can say.
He's setting you up

7
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:56,973
<i>to become the Moraviano</i> principale.

8
00:00:57,057 --> 00:01:00,268
You will become the leader
of the entire syndicate.

9
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:02,604
- <i>Do you feel guilty?</i>
- <i>Guilty about what?</i>

10
00:01:02,687 --> 00:01:04,439
About what we're doing to Mikoy.

11
00:01:04,522 --> 00:01:08,318
Because I'm sure if we hadn't
recruited Mikoy for our mission,

12
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:11,946
maybe by now, he would just be happy
being with Chiara.

13
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:16,576
<i>He would only be thinking about the love</i>
<i>they share and nurture every day, right?</i>

14
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:18,411
<i>Is that real happiness?</i>

15
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:22,916
<i>I want to fully commit to this mission.</i>

16
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:25,960
I'm ready to help you
bring down the Moravianos.

17
00:01:33,593 --> 00:01:34,886
Mikoy?

18
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:40,767
Well… He seems happy with his new role.

19
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:48,733
Your relationship with him

20
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:52,278
gave us a very good cover
to be here in the Philippines.

21
00:01:58,243 --> 00:02:02,580
getting to know the family
of his new partner.

22
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:06,167
Just being happy. Just having fun, right?

23
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:07,669
But I know

24
00:02:07,752 --> 00:02:12,048
there's another reason
why we're here in the Philippines.

25
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:31,401
This is the perfect place
for our center of Moravianos.

26
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:42,120
She looks good in that picture.

27
00:02:58,386 --> 00:03:01,639
And if she wanted to, she could
work anywhere she wants.

28
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,648
Do you suspect her?

29
00:03:11,482 --> 00:03:12,984
Is that why her picture is there?

30
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:21,117
You also can't deny that she has proximity
to the world of the Moravianos

31
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,535
because of her Mommy and Daddy.

32
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:28,541
we still haven't found
any connection to the syndicate.

33
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:30,043
You…

34
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:32,754
What do you think?

35
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:36,925
Do you think she knows
what her Mommy and Daddy are doing?

36
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:42,680
You know, Mikoy is useful.

37
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:45,975
Obviously, that kid
is crazy about you. Right?

38
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:49,187
Possible. But…

39
00:03:50,146 --> 00:03:51,898
He's not like us.

40
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:01,282
Why do you say that?

41
00:04:05,578 --> 00:04:08,498
Like, his outlook on life
is very different.

42
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:24,264
- It's okay, it's okay.
- Thank you for stopping.

43
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:25,556
Stop.

44
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:30,019
- Thank you for your help.
- It's okay. No problem.

45
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:31,271
Are you okay now, ma'am?

46
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:33,564
It's okay.

47
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,987
Maybe you're starting to be like him.

48
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:42,782
We have formidable enemies
here in the Philippines.

49
00:04:45,326 --> 00:04:47,787
Papa! If I'm not tough,

50
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,872
then we would all be dead by now.

51
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:57,171
I'm the reason why we are all still alive.

52
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:06,431
Let me reassure you

53
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:10,476
that nothing will stop our plans
here in the Philippines.

54
00:05:20,611 --> 00:05:22,280
La Morte Bianca,

55
00:05:37,086 --> 00:05:39,297
And you don't need to worry
about that anymore.

56
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,818
Mikoy!

57
00:06:09,952 --> 00:06:12,747
We have to work
in a small team just to make sure

58
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:15,041
that no information will leak

59
00:06:15,124 --> 00:06:18,044
and that our mission
won't get compromised.

60
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:25,426
He will join you
after he recovers from his setback.

61
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:35,436
I admit that at first, we framed him.

62
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:40,108
We blackmailed him
to spy for us on the Moravianos.

63
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,739
Because I realized Agent Alex was right.

64
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:51,536
More people will become victims
of the syndicate.

65
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,872
More people will get hurt.

66
00:06:55,873 --> 00:06:57,667
More people will be dragged into this.

67
00:06:58,876 --> 00:07:02,463
It's just unfortunate that I was the one
who got pulled into this situation.

68
00:07:03,047 --> 00:07:04,298
But you know,

69
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,342
I've thought about it.

70
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:08,344
If not me, then who?

71
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:10,888
If not now,

72
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:12,807
then when?

73
00:07:14,725 --> 00:07:15,768
Right?

74
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:19,272
Maybe there's a reason
why I was placed in this situation.

75
00:07:20,189 --> 00:07:21,566
Maybe…

76
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:26,028
heaven is just giving me
a chance to do the right thing.

77
00:07:34,036 --> 00:07:35,455
Did you use ChatGPT on that?

78
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,665
You definitely didn't write that.
I know you.

79
00:07:37,748 --> 00:07:39,417
What ChatGPT? Hey!

80
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,377
This is not ChatGPT, okay!

81
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,724
Successful? That's easy!

82
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:57,894
We just need to believe
that we can do this!

83
00:07:58,394 --> 00:08:00,313
As a team. Right?

84
00:08:00,396 --> 00:08:03,816
As Linny, Ming-Ming, and Tuck say…

85
00:08:09,071 --> 00:08:10,573
But you know, Mikoy.

86
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,913
We need something stronger.

87
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:19,916
Like… a prayer?

88
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:21,751
You're right!

89
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:24,504
We need the power of prayer.

90
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:30,718
We also need prayers,
and that is very important.

91
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:33,262
But equally important,

92
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:36,349
we also need to train you.

93
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,935
Train?

94
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:43,731
We have to make sure
that you can protect yourself.

95
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:47,443
Because next time,

96
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,904
we might not make it in time
to save your life.

97
00:08:49,987 --> 00:08:52,323
We need to train you,

98
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:56,285
so you can defend yourself
in even more dangerous situations.

99
00:09:12,593 --> 00:09:14,011
Wait! Hold on!

100
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:23,688
Why are you here?

101
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,152
Hey you, Angelito.

102
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:32,572
Why didn't you come over
to your brother's place?

103
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:36,784
Exactly! We waited for you.
Your mother even cooked.

104
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:41,539
I suddenly had something
I needed to finish.

105
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:46,419
By the way, your son is so kind.

106
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:51,507
Wait. Shall we go now?
Let's go! I'll just change first.

107
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:54,302
Oh, why does it seem like
you’re making us leave?

108
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:55,511
Are you hiding something?

109
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:58,598
Wait a second! Here! Love!
Let’s check this one.

110
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:07,106
- I thought you brought a girl here.
- Wait! Under the bed!

111
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:10,484
- That's what I'm saying!
- Really?

112
00:10:10,568 --> 00:10:12,737
- I told you, be careful, love!
- Ouch, ouch.

113
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:15,281
- Be careful, love!
- It hurts.

114
00:10:16,032 --> 00:10:19,118
- Dad! Mom!
- Let me lean first.

115
00:10:19,201 --> 00:10:23,247
I already told you.
That's not on my mind yet.

116
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:27,960
Didn't I promise
that I would finish my studies first?

117
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:30,963
Son, that's right, okay?

118
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:33,591
Just focus on your studies first.

119
00:10:33,674 --> 00:10:35,593
Because I'm sure
you'll have plenty of time

120
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:38,387
for girls once you graduate, okay?

121
00:10:38,971 --> 00:10:41,140
And always be well-behaved, okay?

122
00:10:41,223 --> 00:10:42,558
- Yes.
- Okay.

123
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:45,561
Let’s eat first.

124
00:11:06,123 --> 00:11:08,209
Dear, please forgive your father.

125
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:09,669
Of all people,

126
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:12,838
you should be the one who understands him.

127
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:14,799
He's just worried about you.

128
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:21,889
But when did I let our family down?

129
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,976
And if you ask me,

130
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:31,148
after everything you need to do
for La Morte Bianca,

131
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:45,329
I'm just really happy that I met him.

132
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:02,721
Hi! I am Sofie.

133
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:06,225
Angelito's friend.

134
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,437
Why are you here, dear?

135
00:12:10,187 --> 00:12:11,772
Did you sleep here?

136
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:15,401
Are you my son's girlfriend?

137
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:18,446
Honestly,

138
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:27,121
We are exploring
whether we are a good match.

139
00:12:27,204 --> 00:12:29,290
Whether we are compatible.

140
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:31,542
Whether we fit

141
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:44,305
Oh my, stop right there!

142
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,853
No, but answer me.
Is that what's trendy now?

143
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:52,897
Is that how it is now?

144
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,857
So there are no more labels.

145
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:57,735
It's all just a test drive. Like that?

146
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:05,576
Instead of focusing on labels,

147
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:09,705
we'd rather focus on each other first.

148
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,919
To get to know each other.

149
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:21,008
My Angelito?

150
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:24,595
That's exactly it.

151
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,014
Oh dear!

152
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:30,976
I don't really care
about labels anyway, okay?

153
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:34,605
So it's better if we eat
because we brought a lot of food.

154
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:35,940
- Oh, come on, let's eat.
- I'll excuse myself.

155
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:38,567
Oh, no, no! Sit down there.

156
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:42,238
You both sit down. Because honestly,

157
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:47,284
we need to know
if you're good for our son.

158
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,875
So, sit down. Let's eat.

159
00:13:57,962 --> 00:13:59,255
Let's eat.

160
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:02,716
Come here. Come here.

161
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:25,322
You can also treat this like a friend
you can borrow from when necessary.

162
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:28,033
But just like any friend,

163
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:30,077
there's a proper way to handle it.

164
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:31,537
Your turn.

165
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:37,167
<i>There are four major parts of a gun.</i>

166
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:39,003
<i>This includes the engine, or the action,</i>

167
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:41,589
<i>such as bolt-action or semi-automatic.</i>

168
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:43,799
<i>It’s the heart, or the firing pin.</i>

169
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:46,093
<i>The barrel where</i>
<i>the bullet passes through.</i>

170
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:53,267
<i>The only part of a gun</i>
<i>that is connected to you.</i>

171
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:00,482
<i>You don’t have to change</i>
<i>when you have a gun.</i>

172
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:05,321
<i>Keep calm.</i>

173
00:15:07,281 --> 00:15:09,116
<i>Just like in normal life,</i>

174
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:16,123
<i>It’s like a relationship,</i>

175
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:22,212
<i>And we need to move on</i>
<i>until you hit the right mark.</i>

176
00:15:40,564 --> 00:15:44,944
<i>Do not use it to threaten</i>
<i>or attack anyone.</i>

177
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:48,489
<i>You should never use</i>
<i>your friend for something bad.</i>

178
00:16:32,074 --> 00:16:34,910
It's only been a few days,
and he's already so good at using a gun.

179
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:38,330
It's like… he's even better
than movie actors.

180
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:41,583
The lead movie actor who just does
a montage, a few scenes,

181
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:45,421
then suddenly they're already good
at handling a gun

182
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:47,256
or use any weapon. Right?

183
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:51,635
Just walking down the stairs
and suddenly it's an ultimate makeover.

184
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:53,721
Exactly! Exactly!

185
00:16:55,472 --> 00:16:58,767
I'll admit he's a quick learner
when it comes to weaponry.

186
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:01,061
But he still has a lot to learn.

187
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:26,086
Nice, huh? Wait a second.
I thought we’d do shooting today?

188
00:17:26,795 --> 00:17:27,880
What's this?

189
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:33,218
I think your knowledge of shooting
is enough.

190
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:35,637
This time, self-defense.

191
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:38,474
Self-defense? No offense, okay?

192
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:41,685
As long as I have a gun,
I don't need to learn karate.

193
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:46,065
I’m not trying to brag,
but if anyone tries to violate me,

194
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,149
all I can say is…

195
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:50,152
"You're just one bullet."

196
00:17:52,696 --> 00:17:55,783
But you should not rely on a gun
in every situation.

197
00:17:59,369 --> 00:18:02,539
What if you don't have time
to bring your weapon?

198
00:18:07,336 --> 00:18:10,339
That hurts! Wait! What was that for?

199
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:15,719
That's the problem with close combat.

200
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:17,888
You won't have time to draw your gun.

201
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,973
And more likely,

202
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:22,893
you'll already be down
before you can even move.

203
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:25,062
Okay, fine! Got it!

204
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:27,064
That really hurt.

205
00:18:27,147 --> 00:18:28,649
But you know, you're right.

206
00:18:28,732 --> 00:18:30,609
I really should always be ready.

207
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:33,362
Because you know why I wasn't ready?
Because this can happen.

208
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:35,572
Because look, this can happen.

209
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:38,325
So, you're really right.

210
00:18:38,408 --> 00:18:39,785
Right?

211
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:06,812
You were right.

212
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:10,440
Nice, right?

213
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:25,038
You really learn fast.

214
00:19:25,622 --> 00:19:27,332
I really do learn fast.

215
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:45,559
What are you doing?

216
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:49,354
What do you mean, what am I doing?

217
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:50,772
Do you want me to say it?

218
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:52,024
First,

219
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:55,194
you enter my room without permission.

220
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:57,029
You sleep on my bed.

221
00:19:57,112 --> 00:20:00,574
And now, you’re telling my mom and dad

222
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:02,034
that we’re in a relationship?

223
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:07,456
Correction. I never claimed
that we’re in a relationship.

224
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:12,586
As a matter of fact,
what I said was, we have no label.

225
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:15,589
Even so!

226
00:20:15,672 --> 00:20:18,634
You shouldn’t just barge
into my life without permission.

227
00:20:22,095 --> 00:20:25,432
I don’t know how you get into my room.

228
00:20:25,515 --> 00:20:28,769
So, please, stop invading my privacy!

229
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:30,562
You know what?

230
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:32,981
If you were decent,

231
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:36,610
you’d know it’s not right
to sleep around with just anyone.

232
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:40,239
You don’t even look homeless.

233
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:44,117
If this is just some fun for you,

234
00:20:44,201 --> 00:20:45,410
please…

235
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:48,580
don’t drag me into it. Please.

236
00:20:53,001 --> 00:20:54,503
So, don’t add to it.

237
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:56,964
Please.

238
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:20,279
Bok?

239
00:21:21,488 --> 00:21:24,658
- Are you okay?
- Hey! Don’t scare me like that!

240
00:21:25,325 --> 00:21:28,954
Why? Did I say something wrong?
I just asked if you were okay.

241
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:31,748
What do you need? Why are you here?

242
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:39,464
So, I asked Rafa where you were.
You said you had

243
00:21:39,548 --> 00:21:41,800
a self-defense session with our asset.

244
00:21:41,883 --> 00:21:43,468
So I came here.

245
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:45,429
Why?

246
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:49,558
He has a new lead on our case.

247
00:21:52,394 --> 00:21:53,520
Just follow, okay?

248
00:22:05,949 --> 00:22:07,326
Gosh.

249
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:12,122
Hey!

250
00:22:12,914 --> 00:22:13,790
Chiara.

251
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:21,214
Do you know how long I waited?

252
00:22:22,924 --> 00:22:27,262
I kept calling you,
but you weren’t answering.

253
00:22:29,639 --> 00:22:31,016
You know,

254
00:22:36,313 --> 00:22:39,816
I hope you can make time
for the two of us.

255
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:46,490
It was better when we were in Prague.

256
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,826
At least there, I had you to myself.

257
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:51,620
Now?

258
00:22:52,954 --> 00:22:55,373
You’re like an OFW.

259
00:22:55,999 --> 00:22:59,586
I barely see you. I can’t even find you.

260
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:08,386
You’re right. I’ve just
been overwhelmed with work.

261
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:10,639
But…

262
00:23:12,808 --> 00:23:14,059
I’ll make it up to you.

263
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:22,359
Make it up?

264
00:23:23,902 --> 00:23:25,362
How will you make it up?

265
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:29,407
Do you have chocolates?

266
00:23:29,991 --> 00:23:31,827
Or even flowers?

267
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:36,498
You know, one of my ex-boyfriends,

268
00:23:41,878 --> 00:23:44,089
Just to make it up to me.

269
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:53,682
Another ex-boyfriend of mine,
he hired Bruno Mars to serenade me.

270
00:23:57,102 --> 00:24:00,313
How will Mr. Pinagpala make it up to me?

271
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:18,874
Well, he loves her.

272
00:24:19,499 --> 00:24:21,376
Why did he leave her at the altar?

273
00:24:21,459 --> 00:24:25,380
I thought they were going
to stand by their love.

274
00:24:26,047 --> 00:24:28,925
It's because Matteo is threatening him.

275
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:30,760
If they continue the wedding,

276
00:24:30,844 --> 00:24:33,555
then the man she loves would be killed.

277
00:24:48,778 --> 00:24:52,365
Sir. I’m sorry. I’ve been
looking for Agent Alex.

278
00:24:54,618 --> 00:24:56,578
I called you here

279
00:24:56,661 --> 00:24:59,581
because I want to introduce
someone to you.

280
00:25:29,736 --> 00:25:31,363
<i>Let’s just meet tomorrow.</i>

281
00:25:38,370 --> 00:25:40,163
<i>He is the leader</i>

282
00:25:40,247 --> 00:25:43,792
<i>of the local syndicate</i>
<i>called Sinigang Cartel.</i>

283
00:25:43,875 --> 00:25:45,919
so when the Moravianos
arrived in the country,

284
00:25:48,046 --> 00:25:51,883
<i>Moravianos on the one hand,</i>
<i>Sinigang Cartel on the other one.</i>
